'''Seed-partners''' were small thorn-covered organisms that originated within the [[tampasi]], from the tree-like [[bora]]s, of the living planet [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]]. As Sekot's self-proclaimed "children ... cells in my body,"<ref name="Rogue Planet">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref> the seed-partners would be introduced to a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] who desired to possess one of [[Sekotan Personal Starship|Sekot's living ships]]. If the seed-partners, according to their own desire, attached themselves to the spacer, a ship would be produced by those partners working with a team of [[Ferroan]] designers, [[Langhesi]] forgers, and giant-like [[Jentari]] shapers.

Seed-partners attached themselves to a spacer using a spike, which produced an uncomfortable adhesion, but no wound. Three seed-partners per spacer was the normal outcome of this election process, but in the case of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], fifteen seed partners chose to become part of their new vessel, the ''[[Jabitha]]''.

